The paper deals with a communication problem involving lossless transmission and degraded helpers, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The problem also has applications in cooperative communication schemes (cs.NI) and multimedia communication (cs.MM). The use of auxiliary random variables and optimization techniques suggests a possible connection to signal processing (cs.SI) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
